The paper deals with the secure and reliable connectivity of wireless sensor networks, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the security aspect of the network, which can be categorized under computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of random graphs and Erdős–Renyi graphs in modeling the network suggests that the paper may also belong to the field of theoretical computer science (cs.THE) or algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
